At the completion of this course, the students will be able to

1) Gain fundamental concepts of the general circulation of the atmosphere and oceans;

2) Understand how they are simulated in climate models;

3) Develop the ability to analyze and explain climate phenomena, including human-related climate change, based on climate modeling results.

